**Q8: How do you collect a Flow safely on Android?**

**A:** In a Fragment/Activity:
```kotlin
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
  repeatOnLifecycle(Lifecycle.State.STARTED) {
    vm.state.collect { render(it) }
  }
}
```
`repeatOnLifecycle(STARTED)` starts collection when the view becomes STARTED and cancels it when it drops below STARTED (fragment hidden/destroyed) — restarting each time the view becomes visible again. This is the modern equivalent of LiveData's lifecycle awareness. In **Jetpack Compose**: `val state by vm.state.collectAsStateWithLifecycle()` — same behavior, one-liner. **What you SHOULDN'T do:** plain `launch { vm.state.collect { ... } }` — this keeps collecting while the view is destroyed, wasting work and potentially crashing.
